# .env.example — optional starter template
#
# Jadu itself needs NO secrets. Its workflows only read/write Markdown files
# (TASKS.md, WORKLOG.md, ...) and run git — there is nothing here Jadu requires.
#
# This file exists only as a convenience for PROJECTS that adopt Jadu and do need
# secrets (API keys, tokens, service creds). Copy it to `.env`, fill in real values,
# and keep `.env` out of git (see .gitignore). Commit only this template, keys-only,
# never real values.
#
# Delete the lines you don't need and add your own.

# --- Common examples (uncomment and fill in as needed) ---
# ANTHROPIC_API_KEY=
# OPENAI_API_KEY=
# GITHUB_TOKEN=
